<h1>To Thomas Knox</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir,</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Mount Vernon Virga 26th December 1757</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Your favour of the 28th September came to hand the 20th Instt.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> My Goods, that is such part as you have sent me I am told will be round from Rappahannock River shortlyI cant help expressing great concern, and some Surprize at your not sending the following Articles, which were Included in an Invoice sent the 18th Jany last, the Receipt of which you acknowledge (viz.)<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
<ul class="simple">
	    <li>4 dozn plaid Hose</li>
	    <li> dozn Scythes &amp; Stones<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0003-ptr">3</a></li>
	    <li>4 Curry Combs &amp; Brushes</li>
	    <li>1 Dozn Weeding Hoes</li>
	    <li>1 dozn narrow &amp;  dozn Grubg Do</li>
	    <li>20<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">M</span> 8d. Nails<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0004-ptr">4</a></li>
	    <li>20<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">M</span> 10d. Ditto10<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">M</span> 20d.</li>
	    <li>20<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">M</span> 4d. Ditto 5<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">M</span> 6d. and</li>
	    <li>1 Dozn Logwood Axes.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0005" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0005-ptr">5</a></li>
	  </ul>
<p>These are Articles Sir, I greatly wanted, and must now be obligd to buy in the Country for this years use at exorbitant prices and that perhaps after sending over good part of the Country before they can be procurd.</p>
<p>On board the Nugent Only I have 14 Hogsheads Tobo of the best Mountn Sweetscentedyour best endeavours in the Sales will be exerted I hope in my favourTobo of the like kind, sent by my acquaintances to the London Market commands great prices, and this of mine made upon the same sort of Land as theirs is and handled equally as Neat will, I flatter myself, sell full as high in that of Bristol.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0006" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0006-ptr">6</a></p>
<p>The nett proceeds of this Latter, and Balle of the former Tobo please to pay to Mr Richd Washington of London, who is directed to draw upon you to the amount. Please also to Insure one hundd pounds on the 14 Hogsheads, a Sum much less than the value of the Tobacco but I choose to risk partI doubt not of hearing from you soon &amp; receiving Accounts of Sales, &amp; Acct Currt. I am Sir Yr Most Obedt Hble Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Go: Washington</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-05-02-pb-0073">[73]</span>
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 The letter-book copy is in GWs later hand.</p>


   <p>GW placed his first order with Thomas Knox, a merchant in Bristol, England, on 6 Dec. 1755.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Knoxs letter has not been found. According to GWs ledger, GW sent at some point in 1757 eight hogsheads of tobacco to Thomas Knox aboard the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">King of Prussia</span>, for which he showed credit from Knox of 42.2.5 sterling (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Manuscript Ledger Book 1, 1750-72, in George Washington Papers, Library of Congress. ]">Ledger A</span>, 16).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Neither GWs invoice nor Knoxs acknowledgment has been found, but see Knoxs Invoice, 28 Sept. 1757<span class="choice deletion" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Deleted: ', printed above' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2014-11-06]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><img alt="deletion" src="images/deletion_mark-trans.png" style="border:none;vertical-align: text-bottom; padding-right:2px"/></span>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Knox sent GW six Scythestones, or whetstones, on 18 Aug. 1758.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">M</span> is used here as a symbol for thousand.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0005">5</a>
   
   <p>Knox sent these articles, as well as those listed in GWs letters of <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0047" class="document">30 Dec. 1757</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0060" class="document">January 1758</a>, in August 1758. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0319" class="document">Thomas Knoxs Invoice, 18 Aug. 1758</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0044-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>The master of the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Nugent Only</span> was John Copithorne. GWs ledger shows in his account with Knox a credit of 78.1.5 sterling for the fourteen hogsheads plus 7.11 from the premiums paid on the insurance on both the tobacco and the British goods during transit.</p>

</div>
</div>
